The role of pathological changes of biliopancreatoduodenal zone in development of postcholecystectomy syndrome. Study of the role of biliopancreatoduodenal pathological changes in the development of postcholecystectomy syndrome.Diagnostic complex, including endosonography has been performed in 138 patients with calculous cholecystitis with a significant risk of choledocholithiasis and 112 patients with postcholecystectomy syndrome.The same spectrum of pathological changes of biliopancreatoduodenal zone in both groups was discovered.The pathological changes of biliopancreatoduodenal zone in patients with postcholecystectomy syndrome most likely to appear before the operation.